The same rating organization gives its highest credit rating to the $180 million senior class. Since this is the most
senior class, has the highest possible credit rating, and all prior enhancements are performance risk-free, risk-based
capital would be calculated at the 20% risk-weight. Table 1 summarizes this example. 




